## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Pages & Routing:
  - /settings/settings-dashboard (SettingsDashboard)
  - /settings/user-profile (UserProfilePage)
  - /settings/integrations (IntegrationsCard area)
  - Nested routes for per-section detail views as needed
- State Management:
  - Local component state for section toggles; global state for user permissions
  - Use React useState/useEffect with proper defaults; store arrays as [] via useState<Type[]>([])
- UI Components:
  - Reusable Card component with consistent theming, hover shadows, and focus rings
  - Toggle components with accessible ARIA attributes
  - List/Table components that render with defensive guards for possibly missing data
  - Form elements with consistent dark styling and focus states
  - Credential input sections with masked fields and vault-safe handling hints
- Data Handling:
  - Fetch settings and profile data via API endpoints; guard responses: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - For Supabase-like results, use const items = data ?? [] before mapping
  - Normalize all inputs; trim strings; validate required fields
- Accessibility:
  - Keyboard navigable, semantic landmarks, ARIA roles for sections and dialogs
  - Color contrast adherence per WCAG for interactive states
- Performance:
  - Debounce search/filter in lists; pagination for large rosters
  - Prefetch common data when navigating to settings

### Backend
- APIs:
  - GET /settings/global to fetch global settings (notifications, privacy, autopilot, integrations, data export settings)
  - PATCH /settings/global to update global settings
  - GET /settings/profile to fetch user profile data
  - PATCH /settings/profile to update user profile data
  - GET /integrations (list adapters and status)
  - POST /integrations/:id/connect to initiate/validate connection
  - GET /integrations/:id/credentials to fetch credentials (secure consumption)
  - PATCH /integrations/:id/credentials to update credentials
  - GET /api-keys to list API keys
  - POST /api-keys to create a new API key
  - DELETE /api-keys/:keyId to revoke
  - POST /security/enable-2fa to enable 2FA
  - GET /billing/summary to fetch billing
  - GET /audit/run/:id to fetch run artifacts
- Database schema considerations:
  - users(id, name, email, roles, tenant_id, settings_ref)
  - settings_global(id, notification_preferences JSON, privacy JSON, autopilot JSON, data_export JSON, etc.)
  - integrations(id, name, type, status, credentials_ref, connected_at, user_id)
  - api_keys(id, user_id, key, created_at, last_used_at, status)
  - roles(id, name, permissions JSON)
  - team_members(team_id, user_id, role_id, invited_at, status)
  - billing(id, user_id, plan, usage, invoices JSON)
  - audit_runs(id, actor_id, action, target, timestamp, artifacts JSON)
- Validation & Security:
  - Validate inputs server-side; enforce RBAC for each endpoint
  - Credential management: store credentials securely (vault-like, encrypted at rest)
  - Ensure all endpoints return consistent shapes; guard against nulls
  - Rate limiting and action confirmations for destructive operations
- Data Safety:
  - All operations that mutate data must be idempotent where possible
  - Provide audit trail for changes; support rollback where feasible

### Integration
- Integrations & Adapter System:
  - A pluggable adapter registry that discovers adapters via a central manifest
  - Adapters implement a standard interface: initialize(), testConnection(), fetchCapabilities(), authenticate(credentials), fetchData(payload)
  - CredentialManager provides secure storage and retrieval of credentials per adapter
  - Admin/RBAC controls who can configure adapters, test connections, or rotate credentials
  - Per-adapter UI: connection status, last sync, configuration fields, test buttons
- Data Flow:
  - Settings page reads global settings and per-adapter state via /settings/global and /integrations
  - User Profile page pulls data from /settings/profile
  - API keys and billing data are fetched via dedicated endpoints and exposed in UI
  - All UI actions call proper APIs; optimistic UI updates guarded with fallback to server state
- Error Handling:
  - Centralized error boundaries; user-friendly error messages
  - Retry policies for transient failures; explainable error details for audit logs

## User Experience Flow
1) User lands on Settings & Preferences from the main navigation
2) Left rail lists major sections: Global Settings, User Profile, Integrations, Data & Security, Billing, Exports
3) User selects a section (e.g., Integrations)
   - Adapter list renders with status, description, and action buttons
   - User can add/connect a new adapter, enter credentials, test connection
4) User toggles Notification Preferences; saves, with a toast confirmation
5) User configures Privacy/Data settings: retention policy, export, delete; initiates export if needed
6) User configures Team & RBAC: invites new members, assigns roles, configures SSO
7) User configures Autopilot Defaults: sets thresholds, safety rails
8) User accesses Data Export panel to run or schedule exports; review artifacts
9) From Settings, user navigates to User Profile to manage personal information, security (2FA), API keys, and billing summary
10) All actions generate an audit trail and can be reversed where supported; a run artifact view (AuditTrailPanel) provides detailed history

## Technical Specifications

- Data Models:
  - UserProfile: id, name, email, avatar, twoFAEnabled, twoFABackupCodes, connectedIntegrations[]
  - SettingsGlobal: id, notifications JSON, privacy JSON, team RBAC JSON, autopilot JSON, dataExport JSON
  - IntegrationAdapter: id, name, type, status, credentialsRef, capabilities, lastConnected
  - CredentialStore: id, adapterId, secretMeta, encryptedPayload
  - APIKey: id, userId, key, createdAt, lastUsedAt, status
  - BillingSummary: id, userId, plan, usage, invoices JSON
  - AuditRun: id, actorId, action, target, timestamp, artifacts JSON
- API Endpoints (examples):
  - GET /settings/global
  - PATCH /settings/global
  - GET /settings/profile
  - PATCH /settings/profile
  - GET /integrations
  - POST /integrations/:id/connect
  - GET /integrations/:id/credentials
  - PATCH /integrations/:id/credentials
  - GET /api-keys
  - POST /api-keys
  - DELETE /api-keys/:keyId
  - GET /billing/summary
  - GET /export/history
  - POST /export/schedule
  - GET /audit/run/:id
- Security:
  - JWT/OIDC authentication; RBAC gates on endpoints
  - Data at rest encryption for credentials
  - CSRF protection on mutating endpoints
  - Input validation and schema validation on both sides
- Validation:
  - Response shapes validated: const data = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - Supabase-like fetch results guarded with data ?? []
  - Use optional chaining for nested API data
  - Destructure with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}
- Validation Rules:
  - Email fields validated for proper format
  - Passwords or secrets masked in UI
  - Required fields present for adapter connections
  - Export schedules must include timezone awareness
- Performance & Reliability:
  - Debounce network calls in settings search or filters
  - Paginate large lists (teams, adapters) with lazy loading
  - Caching strategies for static settings to minimize repeated fetches

