=== TASK ===
# Settings & Preferences

## Overview
Develop a comprehensive Settings & Preferences module for LifeOps that provides global application configuration, user profile management touchpoints, and an extensible integrations/adapters system. This initiative includes: notification preferences, privacy controls, team settings, RBAC (roles-based access control), integrations and autopilot defaults, and data export capabilities. It also encompasses a dedicated User Profile Management experience to view/manage account data, connected integrations, API keys, security settings, billing, and module preferences. An extensible Integrations & Adapter System should be pluggable, with standardized interfaces and credential management for external APIs (LLM providers, GitHub, Plaid, Stripe, QuickBooks, and Health APIs). The UI should be consistent with LifeOps design language, provide robust runtime safety for all data interactions, and support a scalable RBAC-driven permissions model across pages and components.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- Settings & Preferences is the global control center for a LifeOps installation. It consolidates user-facing and admin-facing configuration topics: notification preferences, privacy/data controls, team settings and RBAC, integration adapters, autopilot defaults (governance of automated workflows), and data export/export deletion workflows. It also surfaces a gateway to the User Profile Page and Integrations/Adapters subsystem.

Goals:
- Centralize global configuration with modular sections:
  - Notification preferences (email, push, in-app)
  - Privacy and data governance (data retention, export, delete)
  - Team management and RBAC (invite, roles, SSO settings)
  - Integrations and Adapter System (credentials, onboarding, status)
  - Autopilot defaults (automation behavior, thresholds, safety rails)
  - Data export/import tooling and run artifacts
- Provide a seamless bridge to:
  - User Profile Management: account data, connected integrations, API keys, security settings (2FA), billing summary, module preferences
  - Integrations & Adapter System: pluggable adapters with a unified interface and credential management
- Ensure robust security, auditability, and reversible actions with a complete run artifact trail
- UI should be navigable via a left-side navigation rail and a top breadcrumb/header bar, with dense information presentation suitable for power users

Connected features and UI implications:
- User Profile Management: A sub-area or route from Settings that shows account data, connected integrations, API keys, security (2FA), billing, and module preferences
- Integrations & Adapter System: A pluggable adapter layer with a credentials vault, standardized interfaces, capability discovery, and per-adapter configuration
- Data flows must guard against nulls and undefined values; all Supabase results must be guarded with data ?? [] and Array.isArray checks
- Permissions: Actions and visibility governed by RBAC rules; show/hide sections based on user roles; ensure safe defaults

UI elements and how they should look:
- Notification Preferences: tri-state toggles or on/off toggles with per-channel granularity (email, push, in-app)
- Privacy & Data: data retention options, export data controls (export now, schedule export), delete data requests workflow
- Team & Roles: team roster, invite modal, role assignments, SSO settings
- Autopilot Defaults: toggles for suggested-only vs autopilot decisions, thresholds, and safety rails
- Integrations: list of available adapters with status indicators, credential management UI, test/validate connection actions
- User Profile Page: account info fields, connected integrations list, security (2FA), API keys management, billing summary, module preferences
- Visual language: consistent dark UI with the provided color palette, elevated cards, left navigation, and accent indicators for active/incomplete items

